<item>
            <title>[LU-7149] Test framework doesn&apos;t cleanup so test always passed when executed consecutively</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7149</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Test 224c sanity.sh always passed when executed consecutively. Even when executed without fix and expected to be failed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But test_224c fails as expected with timeout if run ONLY=224c sh sanity.sh on fresh created lustre.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that some tests set off writethrough, using &quot;set_cache writethrough off&quot; and don&apos;t restore it before 224c, that needs writethrough to be set on.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
